<subSubSection id="56D4E16354F86CD50D52509D8D3DB11F" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="description">
<paragraph id="7E0F0E4C55C092BF7242D91BAA4F45F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D14AD18805E947C92FF26EDBEAEE2652" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="287539B2A608D8FF078D6D8CFD25693B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Measurements of male</emphasis>
: BL: 13.67 mm, FL: 8.12 mm. HL: 2.26 mm, HW: 2.91 mm, EYL: 0.74 mm, TL: 1.24 mm, PL: 2.75 mm, PW: 2.34 mm, EL: 3.55 mm, EW: 3.59 mm. HW/HL: 1.29, TL/EYL: 1.68, PL/PW: 1.18, EL/EW: 0.99.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="98680C7AF04AE4ABAAA18F051CA4BF9F" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Head metallic dark blue to violaceous blue, pronotum and elytra metallic dark blue to violaceous with purplish hue; abdomen with segments III-VI black, segment VII black with posterior margin broadly reddish-yellow, segments VIII and X entirely reddish-yellow, segment IX reddish-yellow with apical half of latter blackish; antennae black, base and apex of segment 1 and 2 reddish, four outer segments creamy white; mandibles black, medial margin and distal portion of mandible dark reddish-brown; maxillary and labial palpi deep black, last segments sometimes slightly paler brownish.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="68A026E35381A938F3D8D36EF2BF8B42" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
Head (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9E3A2B5BEB40E8F3BE7275C0D029E100" captionStart="Figures 9–12" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 9 - 12. Head of species of subgenus Hesperosoma Hesperosoma 9 H. chenchangchini sp. nov. 10 H. puetzi 11 H. xizangense sp. nov. 12 H. languidum sp. nov. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1075.75799.figures9-12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/620006" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">11</figureCitation>
) 1.29 times as wide as long, rounded trapezoid, tempora narrowed towards neck in regular arc, eyes moderately protruding; surface with dense and coarse punctation, mostly contiguous; with short, weakly delimited impunctate mid-line, extending from frons to about half of mid-length; antennae with segments 4-8 markedly oblong, segments 9 and 10 about as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ADAB3E12F773CB9C441818B195E04416" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Pronotum 1.18 times as long as wide, widest at level of large lateral seta, narrowed towards base in wide, but shallow concave arc; surface as densely and coarsely punctate as on head, with indistinct, short impunctate mid-line in posterior third; scutellum with dense and pit-like punctation, interstices forming small transverse rugae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D3098119CDE899F47AEF1D251EF54F2F" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Elytra as long as wide, exceedingly densely, coarsely punctate, punctures almost contiguous.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="06CBDB3240B4CAAB880340BEC1298F3D" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Abdominal tergites III-V with basal transverse depression, punctation of abdominal tergites III-V large, but feeble at base; posterior halves of abdominal tergites III-V and entire surface of remaining tergites with very fine and dense punctuation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="836055633C759B5FFC7B382F86898B77" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="560804ACF1CA5B943E30F653168954F4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Male.</emphasis>
Protarsomeres 1-4 moderately dilated, heart-shaped; sternite VII with patch of long yellow setae on median portion and posterior margin broadly emarginate at middle; sternite VIII with posterior margin emarginate at middle; aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation id="83B906703592A2C62E85B646E140FFB6" captionStart="Figures 53–57" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 53 - 57. Hesperosoma xizangense sp. nov. 53 - 54 habitus 55 - 57 aedeagus, lateral (55) and ventral (56) views, paramere (57). Scale bars: 2 mm (53 - 54), 0.2 mm (55 - 57)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1075.75799.figures53-57" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/620014" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">55-57</figureCitation>
) very similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="DAC76E9FF902450AD2AB73D688B56F8F" genus="H." lsidName="H. puetzi" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="puetzi">
<emphasis id="E11A8F78E3C8E612DCABABF303BF1630" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">H. puetzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DF489F0E0429F88BFBA5C749193B853F" genus="H." lsidName="H. xizangense" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="xizangense">
<emphasis id="743223689A46769341FC38E355A46D6F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">H. xizangense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., but markedly larger, median lobe and paramere slightly asymmetrical, paramere (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4312043B69E7F4265EC77E09CF1EFCA2" captionStart="Figures 53–57" captionStartId="F11" captionText="Figures 53 - 57. Hesperosoma xizangense sp. nov. 53 - 54 habitus 55 - 57 aedeagus, lateral (55) and ventral (56) views, paramere (57). Scale bars: 2 mm (53 - 54), 0.2 mm (55 - 57)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1075.75799.figures53-57" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/620014" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">57</figureCitation>
) shorter than median lobe and slightly bent to left side in ventral view.
</paragraph>
