<paragraph id="9A4825D27EB847F2C372A24F1F65D28D" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="35DCD4366CF1D9A9A643D9CFCC74D234" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">The species is named after the type locality</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5261AFAECF701272F8D993C8545B5AC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F668BCFA4C65865A56B3C8CD0E317E4C" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="513F458D594680E4FCBE45535F708422" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">China (Xizang).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C98F40C46913BDFC0304E3345354F850" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="833DDEF41B6A43AE6A002CE78D964ADA" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E1ED3F5EA8951C5F52F9AB2B43B2CF03" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">
The new species is very similar externally to 
<taxonomicName id="DC90A2D93D3390FD32D7D0088F76E89E" genus="H." lsidName="H. languidum" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="languidum">
<emphasis id="3385A36E76C83C5D8512BB215C28EA1A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">H. languidum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Yunnan) and 
<taxonomicName id="EF9ED7F3250983A77EBA55D57BF76A34" genus="H." lsidName="H. puetzi" pageId="0" pageNumber="137" rank="species" species="puetzi">
<emphasis id="F529A1F1EB6947E0A5385BDDA48AA1CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="137">H. puetzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Sichuan), but can be recognised by the emarginated anterior margin of frons (Figs 
